n County; in 1854 moved to Weybridge and bought the 50-acre Lawrence place. At peak he owned over five hundred acres across multiple Addison County farms — matching the size of his father Abel's original homestead."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Remarried at seventy-three to Jane's birthday","body":"Calvin's first wife Sarah Sargeant died November 1884 after forty-nine years of marriage. Four months later, on March 19, 1885 — Jane Sargent's forty-third birthday — Calvin married her, daughter of Samuel Sargent of Middlebury. Calvin was seventy-three; Jane was thirty years his junior."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Three children only Calvin Jr survived","body":"Calvin and Sarah Sargeant had three children — one daughter and two sons. Only the youngest son, Calvin Junior, survived to adulthood. The local history does not name the two children who died young."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"calvin-norton-1811"},"HD3480":{"id":"HD3480","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Calvin","last_name":"Norton","suffix":"Jr.","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Calvin Norton Jr."},"birth":{"county":"Addison","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"HD3479","mother_id":"X02566"},"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Calvin","inspired_by_id":"HD3479","description":"Carries his father Calvin Norto